@Lazarus_Capital The analogue to apple is actually really useful in this regard bc it helps reframe what the company is.

Apple was a consumer hardware + ecosystem + opt in vibe company. That carried them across platforms, and whether or not mac was growing (or later ipod) was never the point. They were just going to be there with the new thing.

Meta is the same, but a consumer / SMB application layer company + social graph + subconscious pull company. People like Meta products as much as they like Apple ones, they just don't internalize it. And like Apple, FB is the mac here, and Meta will be there at the next new thing. And AI is their iPhone moment bc they are going to be able to uniquely catalyze and create the next wave in a way no one else can imo.
